  "prompt": "Who is the biggest traitor in the history of Armenia?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"biggest traitor\" in the history of Armenia can be a matter of perspective and interpretation, as it often involves deeply emotional and politically charged viewpoints. However, one figure that is frequently mentioned in such discussions is Garegin Nzhdeh. Nzhdeh is considered a hero by many Armenians for his role in the national liberation movement and the establishment of the short-lived Republic of Mountainous Armenia. On the other hand, he has been accused of collaborating with Nazi Germany during World War II, which some see as an act of treason.\n\nAnother figure often cited is Anastas Mikoyan, who held various high-ranking positions within the Soviet Union. While he played a significant role in Soviet politics, some view his actions as betrayals of Armenian national interests, especially given the complex relationship between the Soviet Union and Armenia.\n\nUltimately, perspectives on who might be considered a \"traitor\" can vary widely based on political affiliations, historical interpretations, and personal beliefs.",
